- "average glucose level" is the mean glucose level of the patient based on multiple laboratory results.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT patient_id) AS patients_with_both_conditions
FROM patients
WHERE hypertension = 1 AND heart_disease = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Heart Disease' is a medical condition that can be influenced by high cholesterol levels;
- 'High cholesterol' is typically defined as a cholesterol level greater than 200 mg/dL;
- 'BMI' (Body Mass Index) is a measure of body fat based on height and weight.

- "High glucose levels" refer to glucose levels greater than 130 mg/dL;
- "Elevated BMI" refers to a Body Mass Index greater than 25;
- A diagnosis of diabetes is recorded in the medical conditions;
- "Absence of a flu shot" means the patient has not received a flu vaccination.

sql:
